headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet and Scottie Barnes scored 19 points apiece, Pascal Siakam added 16 points and 11 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the Orlando Magic 102-89 on Friday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors beat Magic 102-89 for fifth straight win

headlines.description: — Once introductions for the game against the Dallas Mavericks were complete Friday night, Kentavious Caldwell-Pope delivered a direct message to Washington Wizards teammate Kristaps Porzingis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 24 against Mavericks as Wizards win 135-103

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 32 points and Jayson Tatum had 31 to help the Boston Celtics stop a rare late-season stumble and beat the Indiana Pacers 128-123 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Tatum pair up to lead Celtics past Pacers 128-123

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 25 points, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Houston Rockets 122-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 25 in Kings' 2nd win over Rockets in 3 days

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 30 points and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Phoenix Suns 122-114 on Friday night in a matchup of the NBA’s top two teams, extending their winning streak to seven.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks leads short-handed Grizzlies past Suns, 122-114

headlines.description: — On a night when both the Milwaukee Bucks and Los Angeles Clippers rested their top guys, Robert Covington made the most of an opportunity for additional playing time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rip Bucks 153-119 as both teams rest top players

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Killian Hayes scored a career-high 26 points and Frank Jackson also had 26 to lead the Detroit Pistons to a 110-101 victory over Oklahoma City on Friday night in a matchup of teams near the bottom of the NBA standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayes and Jackson muscle Pistons to 9-point win over Thunder

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell had 22 points, Keldon Johnson added 21 points and the San Antonio Spurs maintained their hold on 10th place in the Western Conference by defeating the Portland Trail Blazers 130-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs maintain 10th place in West with big win over Blazers

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Timberwolves are still polishing their playoff credentials and Karl-Anthony Towns gave a sneak peek Friday night of just what type of challenge they'd present in the postseason.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Edwards lead Timberwolves to 136-130 win over Nuggets

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 32 points, Brandon Ingram added 29 against his former team and the New Orleans Pelicans spoiled Anthony Davis' return from injury with another fourth-quarter rally in a 114-111 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans rally past Lakers 114-111 despite Davis' return
